Exercise 97: Elegant printing of an array

Implement the method public static int printElegantly(int[] array), which prints the numbers
in the array on the same row. In the printout all the numbers should be separated with comma
and whitespace and there should not be a comma trailing the last number.

Program skeleton:

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] array = {5, 1, 3, 4, 2};
        printElegantly(array);
    }

    public static void printElegantly(int[] array) {
        // write code here
    }
}

The output should be:

5, 1, 3, 4, 2
